CALL

Syntax: call <object>
        call <object>;<function>
        call <object>;<function>;<arg>
        call <object>;<function>;<arg>;<arg>

Note: Do not use angle brackets in actual commands.
  Write:   call splynncryth;query_level
  Not:     call <splynncryth>;query_level

Calls a named function on a named object, passing any arguments you
provide. If no function is specified, a dump of the object's state
is printed using the default query functions. Both <object> and
<function> may be arrays (e.g. "users").

The object argument accepts the same references as the refs command:
a player name, a path, "users" for all connected players, or a
numeric ref from a previous command result.

EXAMPLES

  Dump an object (no function):
    call kira
    call /daemon/rifts_combat

  Call a single query function:
    call kira;query_level
    call kira;query_race

  Set a stat (e.g. HP, MDC, SDC):
    call kira;set_stats;HP;200
    call kira;set_stats;MDC;300
    call kira;set_stats;max_MDC;300

  Set a property:
    call kira;set_property;mdc_creature;1
    call kira;set_property;rifts_slot;armor

  Set an environment variable:
    call kira;setenv;autododge;1

  Read an environment variable:
    call kira;getenv;autododge

  Call a function on a daemon:
    call /daemon/rifts_combat;query_version

  Call a function on all connected players:
    call users;query_name
    call users;query_level

WARNING

  call bypasses all safety checks. A wrong function name silently
  fails. A wrong argument type or value can crash the target object
  or corrupt player save data. Test on yourself or on a disposable
  test NPC before running on a live player. Do not use call to set
  values that have proper admin commands (setrole, setfaction, etc.).

